observations: The 3n variants (e2b/e4b) outperform baseline Gemma 3 at similar sizes.
Gemma3-12b does not beat gemma3n-e4b, so variant choice matters more than size.
Gemma3-4b sits near 50% overall, clearly ahead of 1b and 270m but still mid-pack.
Granite4-tiny-h leads the family, edging out granite4-1b and granite4-micro.
Granite3-moe-1b is the weakest, with small MoE variants lagging overall.
Granite3-3-8b and granite3-dense-8b land mid-pack, not clearly better than smaller granite4 variants.
Deepseek-r1-8b is the clear standout, far ahead of the 1.5bâ€“14b cluster.
Deepseek-r1-14b and deepseek-r1-7b cluster around ~50%, with limited gains from size alone.
Josiefied deepseek-r1-0528-qwen3-8b tracks deepseek-r1-7b closely on this test mix.
The VL line is strongest; qwen3-vl-8b achieves a perfect score.
Qwen3-8b and qwen3-14b are very close, suggesting diminishing returns past 8b.
Qwen3 Coder 30B underperforms general Qwen3 models on these math tests.
Qwen3-vl-30b is a negative outlier, weaker than smaller VL variants.
